snippet.textDisplay:
Never full cover potatoes with water!! I come from a family of potato farmers and the leftover "skin" will retain a whole lot more of flavour if you just add about half an inch of water and let them mostly steam.

Just like with rice, the water should be gone when the potatoes are cooked. It will also retain more of the shape and keep the starches more intact which makes an even more amazing mash.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: Sir? Excuse me, Sir? Sir Babish? Yeah I'm going to politely ask you to NEVER EVER call it St. Patty's Day if you come to Ireland. We hate it, and it's not the name. It's St. PADDY's Day. And while you did an amazing job of Shepherd's Pie we never used lamb mince and still called it Shepherds Pie - lamb was, and still is for many,  a celebration meat in Ireland and  beef was a daily thing.
